modules.description: Handles writing image data to files, supporting RGB, RGBA, and grayscale formats. Works with image objects and optional specification and append flags. Useful for saving processed images to disk in various color formats.

This module defines operations to inspect and manipulate image specification metadata, including retrieving shape, base type, and named attributes. It works with structured image descriptions that include dimensions, color space, and custom key-value pairs. Concrete use cases include configuring image processing pipelines and validating input formats before loading or saving operations.

This module handles input operations for reading images from files, supporting RGB color format. It initializes input sources, retrieves image specifications, and provides functions to read image data into typed image structures. Concrete use cases include loading RGB images for pixel processing or visualization workflows.

This module handles image input/output operations for typed image structures, supporting reading and writing RGB, RGBA, and grayscale images with typed error handling. It works with base types like UInt8, Float, and Double, and structured image specifications including dimensions and color spaces. Concrete use cases include loading images for pixel-level manipulation and saving processed images in specific formats.
